to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"cancer\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the bin\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a quadruple sculls gold medal hanging round her neck after pipping the Netherlands in an extraordinary late surge, Anderson's voice cracked with emotion as she recalled her journey and offered a rallying cry to the Olympic champions of the future.\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9390590210459295, \"rank\": 0.06426901852932046, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"score\": 0.9987383565188647, \"rank\": 0.0012632372363446092, \"text\": \"Anderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Anderson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a quadruple sculls\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medal\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 792}, {\"ngram\": \"her neck\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"an extraordinary late surge\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"emotion\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"her journey\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"a rallying cry\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic champions\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I threw that away because I did not believe,\\\" she said, fighting back tears alongside her team-mates Lauren Henry, Hannah Scott and Georgie Brayshaw.\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tears\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"her team-mates Lauren Henry\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"Hannah Scott\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"Georgie Brayshaw\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was 13 at the time so why would you believe?\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Young girls out there struggle a little bit to see themselves as these strong athletic individuals but that's changing now Lola Anderson \\\"Young girls out there struggle a little bit to see themselves as these strong athletic individuals but that's changing now.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Young girls\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"these strong athletic individuals\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"Lola Anderson\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"Young girls\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"these strong athletic individuals\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You have got more and more women taking part in sport.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more and more women\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My dad saw it before I did and saw the potential I had.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My dad\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know he'd be very, very proud if he was here.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It sounds silly because I am nowhere near that point, but all I can think of now, given that my journey started with my dad, is how much I can not wait to show this to my children one day and inspire them.\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"my journey\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"my dad\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"my children\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have not even got a boyfriend!\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a boyfriend\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this is something I want for my family current and want for my family to come.\\\"\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For almost the entirety of their voyage along the 2,000m course on the outskirts of Paris, Britain's fate seemed destined to be silver.\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2045, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8249674516357255e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9830591482941048, \"rank\": 0.017012416849378507, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"almost the entirety\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"their voyage\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"the outskirts\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reigning world and European champions had rapidly found themselves in second place behind the fast-starting Dutch quartet, whose advantage rarely looked like fading.\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2210, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.9530732920466158, \"rank\": 0.03412908619385589, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reigning world\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2115}, {\"ngram\": \"European champions\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"whose advantage\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even with 500m remaining, the British boat was still more than a second down, only to produce the most sensational late surge, seizing the lead with the very last stroke.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.7676850452835203, \"rank\": 0.2934688577274555, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"500m\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2283}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2340}, {\"ngram\": \"the most sensational late surge\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2412}, {\"ngram\": \"the very last stroke\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Victory came in 6 minutes 16.31 seconds - just 0.15sec ahead of the devastated Dutch, who suffered a sense of deja vu after GB had pulled off the identical trick to defeat them at last year's World Championships.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2519, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.9530732920466158, \"rank\": 0.03412908619385589, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8589592315796807, \"rank\": 0.16419960567834024, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Victory\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"6 minutes\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2465}, {\"ngram\": \"16.31 seconds\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2479}, {\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2546}, {\"ngram\": \"the identical trick\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's World Championships\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions The best destinations and activities to book this winter \\\"It was amazing,\\\" said Henry.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2785, \"end\": 2801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Proud\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"Enhanced Games Sports quiz\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2732}, {\"ngram\": \"100 hard questions\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2760}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible year\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2782}, {\"ngram\": \"Grand Slam Track decision\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"2025 ambitions\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"The best destinations\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"activities\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"this winter\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"Henry\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could feel we were moving on the Dutch crew so I was calling to the girls: 'We need to go now'.\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2980, \"end\": 2985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.9530732920466158, \"rank\": 0.03412908619385589, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the girls\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just have 100% belief in the race and 100% belief in each other.\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100% belief\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3081}, {\"ngram\": \"100% belief\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We know that if we deliver our best we will get an outcome like this.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an outcome\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If we ever believe it's over then it is over.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The moment we lose belief, we have lost the race.\", \"from\": 3229, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"belief\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3254}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, no matter how far behind we are, we always have belief until we cross that finish line.\\\"\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"belief\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3337}, {\"ngram\": \"that finish line\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Victory, which was only confirmed by a photo finish, was the perfect way to begin the banishment of Team GB's Tokyo Olympics rowing debacle on the first day of finals at the Paris regatta.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3473, \"end\": 3480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.242938072774357e-13, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3483, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.832745613037967e-15, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3547, \"end\": 3552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8249674516357255e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Victory\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3380}, {\"ngram\": \"a photo finish\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3424}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect way\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3445}, {\"ngram\": \"the banishment\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3469}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain managed just two minor medals in Japan three years ago, where their worst Olympic rowing performance since 1972 was blighted by public infighting.\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9830591482941048, \"rank\": 0.017012416849378507, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3604, \"end\": 3609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5013424640883966, \"rank\": 0.7853158868674821, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just two minor medals\", \"from\": 3579, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"their worst Olympic rowing performance\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3671}, {\"ngram\": \"public infighting\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the customary dominance has started to return in recent years, and the women's quadruple sculls have now completed their set of Olympic, world and European titles.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3885, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the customary dominance\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3745}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 3771, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's quadruple sculls\", \"from\": 3789, \"to\": 3817}, {\"ngram\": \"their set\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 3846}, {\"ngram\": \"world\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3864}, {\"ngram\": \"European titles\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are far from alone in the British ranks.\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3918, \"end\": 3925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.7676850452835203, \"rank\": 0.2934688577274555, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wik